I"s<p>When using <em>OpenVPN</em> on an <em>Ubiquity</em> <strong><em>Edgerouter Lite/X</em></strong>, there is no straight-forward way to reload the OpenVPN daemon when a configuration file is changed.
To reload the OpenVPN daemon after a configuration change, type <code class="highlighter-rouge">configure</code> and then reconfigure the <code class="highlighter-rouge">vtunX</code> interface:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>delete interfaces openvpn vtun0
commit
set interfaces openvpn vtun0 config-file &lt;$OPENVPN_CONFIG_FILE&gt;
commit
save
</code></pre></div></div>

